  "day": 66,
  "key": "day_66_flesh_and_bones",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "It Is I Myself"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "That evening, the disciples were together with the doors locked.",
      "They were afraid."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "appearance",
        "icon": "wb_sunny",
        "label": { "en": "Peace Be With You" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus came and stood among them.",
          "He said,",
          "“Peace be with you.”",
          "They were startled and frightened,",
          "thinking they saw a ghost."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "physical",
        "icon": "pan_tool",
        "label": { "en": "Flesh and Bones" },
        "lines": [
          "He said to them,",
          "“Why are you troubled?",
          "Look at my hands and my feet.",
          "It is I myself!",
          "Touch me and see;",
          "a ghost does not have flesh and bones,",
          "as you see I have.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "evidence",
        "icon": "restaurant",
        "label": { "en": "He Ate in Their Presence" },
        "lines": [
          "While they still did not believe it",
          "because of joy and amazement,",
          "he asked,",
          "“Do you have anything here to eat?”",
          "They gave him a piece of broiled fish,",
          "and he ate it in their presence."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Why do you think Jesus invited them to touch him and watched him eat? What does this suggest about the kind of resurrection the disciples were claiming?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Luke 24:36–43", "John 20:19–20"]
  }
}
